Adjust rack to top position (top and middle positions for 4 servings) and preheat oven to 425 degrees. Wash and dry produce.

In a #medium bowl{}, combine @yogurt{4%tablespoon}, @garlic powder{2%teaspoon}, @Shawarma spice blend{1%tablespoon}, @olive oil{1%tablespoon}, @salt{1%tsp}, and @pepper{}. Add @chicken cutlets{10%ounce} and turn to coat. Set aside to marinate for ~{15%minutes}.

While chicken marinates, wash and dry produce.

Halve, peel, and cut @red onion{1} into 1⁄2-inch-thick wedges; mince a few wedges until you have 2 TBSP. Quarter @grape tomatoes{8%ounce}. Dice @mini cucumber{2}. Pick and roughly chop fronds from @dill{1/4%ounce}. Quarter @lemon{1}.

In a second medium bowl, combine minced onion, tomatoes, cucumbers, half the dill, juice from half the lemon, a large drizzle of @olive oil{}, @salt{}, and @pepper{}. Refrigerate until ready to serve.

Drain and rinse @chickpeas{1}; pat very dry with #paper towels{}.

Toss chickpeas and onion wedges on a #baking sheet{} with a large drizzle of @olive oil{}, @Shawarma spice blend{1%tsp}, @salt{}, and @pepper{}

Roast on top rack, tossing halfway through, until chickpeas are crispy and onion is browned and tender, ~{18-20%minutes}.

> It's natural for chickpeas to pop a bit while roasting!

Meanwhile, roughly chop @pistachios{1/2%ounce}.

Melt @butter{1%TBSP} in a #small pot{} over medium-high heat. Add @dried cherries{1%ounce}, half the pistachios, remaining Shawarma spice blend, and a pinch of @salt{}. Cook, stirring, until fragrant, ~{1%minute}.

Stir in @basmati rice{1/2%cup}, @water{3/4%cup}, and a big pinch of @salt{}. Bring to a boil, then cover and reduce heat to low. Cook until rice is tender, ~{15-18%minutes}. Keep covered off heat until ready to serve.

While rice cooks, heat a drizzle of @olive oil{} in a #large nonstick pan{} over medium heat.

Remove chicken from marinade; allow excess marinade to drip back into bowl. Discard remaining marinade. Add chicken to pan and cook until browned and cooked through, ~{3-5%minutes} per side.

> Lower the heat if chicken begins to brown too quickly.

Transfer chicken to a #cutting board{}.

Wrap @pitas{2} in damp #paper towels{}; microwave until warm and pliable, ~{30-40%seconds}. Carefully cut each pita into six triangles.

Fluff rice with a #fork{}; stir in remaining dill, @butter{1%TBSP}, @salt{}, and @pepper{}. Thinly slice chicken crosswise.

Divide rice between plates; top with chicken and roasted chickpeas and onion in separate sections. Drizzle with as much @tzatziki{1} as you like; garnish with remaining pistachios. Serve with cucumber salad, pita wedges, @classic hummus{1}, and any remaining tzatziki on the side.

> Poultry is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 165°.